text: Interior, 2018 Grace Heritage Center (formerly Grace Episcopal Church) is a church building located at 811 South Main Street in Georgetown, Texas, United States. Built in 1881, the building is the city's oldest wood-framed church. The building was added to the National Register of Historic Places on April 29, 1986, and later removed on February 17, 1999. ==See also== * National Register of Historic Places listings in Williamson County, Texas ==References== ==External links== * Category:1881 establishments in Texas Category:Churches in Texas Category:Former National Register of Historic Places in Texas Category:National Register of Historic Places in Williamson County, Texas Category:Religious buildings and structures completed in 1881
